When using sed for a search and replace operation, which option must be included so thatthe substitution applies to the entire line rather than just the first instance?
A)  g
B)  a
C)  r
D)  y
A
A. The g option, also known as global or greedy, will apply the matched operation tothe entire line rather than just the first instance of the match. The other options apply asthey would for a Perl- Compatible Regular Expression.
